Enable display of series-type custom columns.

cc_exceptions disabled all series-type custom columns to dodge a crash on
calibre-web's internal DB-reconnect path (see janeczku/calibre-web#1501,
#2797). The display path itself works -- setup_db_cc_classes and
detail.html already contain a 'series' branch -- only the exception list
suppresses it. Removing 'series' here exposes the column name and index
in book details, advanced search, and the sidebar. The reconnect crash is
unsolved upstream; a `systemctl restart calibre-web` after a settings
change that triggers internal reload is the workaround.

--- a/cps/db.py
+++ b/cps/db.py
@@ -53,7 +53,7 @@ from .string_helper import strip_whitespaces

 log = logger.create()

-cc_exceptions = ['composite', 'series']
+cc_exceptions = ['composite']
 cc_classes = {}

 Base = declarative_base()
